dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Travnik, sheet Y-24. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Travnik, Yugoslavia. Universal transverse Mercator and North Italy zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1947. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Intelligence reports up to Jan. 1944. Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1944. Map states location as Yugoslavia though the map actually depicts Bosnia and Herzegovina. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1948.
